# Clinical RAG Q&A System

A production-grade, HIPAA-conscious Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline for clinical Q&A, built with LangChain, Pinecone, and GPT-4. Designed to enable clinicians to query large volumes of unstructured clinical notes with high accuracy and sub-200ms response time.

---

## Architecture

```
Raw Clinical Notes (EHR)
        │
        ▼
 PII De-identification
 (Azure Presidio + Custom NER)
        │
        ▼
 Chunking & Embedding
 (Sentence Transformers / OpenAI Embeddings)
        │
        ▼
 Vector Store (Pinecone / FAISS)
        │
   Query Input
        │
        ▼
 Retriever → Re-ranker → LLM (GPT-4 / LLaMA 2)
        │
        ▼
  FastAPI Response Layer
        │
        ▼
  Streamlit UI / API Consumer
```

---

## Features

- **HIPAA-conscious PII scrubbing** before any data reaches the LLM
- **Hybrid retrieval** — dense (vector) + sparse (BM25) with re-ranking
- **Multi-turn conversational memory** using LangChain ConversationBufferWindowMemory
- **Source attribution** — every answer cites the source document and page
- **Evaluation pipeline** — RAGAS metrics: faithfulness, answer relevancy, context recall
- **FastAPI backend** with async endpoints, rate limiting, and structured logging
- **Streamlit UI** for clinician-facing demo
- **Docker-ready** for deployment on AWS ECS / Azure Container Apps

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| LLM | GPT-4 / GPT-4o (OpenAI), LLaMA 2 (fallback) |
| Orchestration | LangChain, LangChain Expression Language (LCEL) |
| Embeddings | OpenAI text-embedding-3-small, Sentence Transformers |
| Vector Store | Pinecone (prod), FAISS (local dev) |
| Re-ranking | Cohere Rerank API |
| PII Scrubbing | Microsoft Presidio + custom spaCy NER |
| API Layer | FastAPI + Uvicorn |
| UI | Streamlit |
| Evaluation | RAGAS |
| Containerization | Docker, Docker Compose |
| Cloud | AWS S3 (document store), AWS Lambda (async jobs) |

